This paper deals with autonomous driving policies and safety assurance in human-robot vehicle interactions, which are topics that fall under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of model predictive control and probabilistic planning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a full-scale steer-by-wire platform, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for perception and decision-making.
